## The Core Problem Explained

| Issue | What Happens | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `0.1 + 0.2 === 0.3` | `false` | Binary can't represent `0.1` or `0.2` exactly |
| `4.99 + 1.99 + 2.50 === 9.48` | `false` | Rounding errors accumulate |
| `1.005.toFixed(2)` | `"1.00"` not `"1.01"` | The stored value is `1.00499999...` |
| `totalCents === 948` | **always `true`** | Integers are exact in IEEE 754 |

### The Golden Rule for Money
> **Store as integer cents → compute in integers → convert to dollars only for display**

This is exactly how **Stripe, PayPal, and every bank API** works — they all require amounts in the smallest currency unit (cents, pence, etc.) for precisely this reason.

