    <div class="explain-grid">

        <div class="explain-block">
            <h4>🧮 IEEE 754 Binary Representation</h4>
            <p>
                JavaScript (and most languages) store decimals as
                <strong>binary fractions</strong> using the IEEE 754 double-precision standard.
                Just as <span class="mono">1/3</span> cannot be written exactly in decimal
                (0.333…), most decimal fractions like <span class="mono">0.1</span> or
                <span class="mono">0.2</span> cannot be stored exactly in binary.
