---

## Why This Matters — The Core Explanation

### The Root Cause: Binary Cannot Represent Most Decimals

| Decimal | What IEEE 754 Actually Stores |
|---------|-------------------------------|
| `0.1` | `0.1000000000000000055511151231257827021181583404541015625` |
| `0.2` | `0.200000000000000011102230246251565404236316680908203125` |
| `0.1 + 0.2` | `0.30000000000000004` ← **not** `0.3` |

### Why `===` Fails

```javascript
// The developer's claim:
0.1 + 0.2 === 0.3   // false  ← silent bug
4.99 + 3.49 + 1.52 === 10.00  // false  ← customer overcharged
19.99 * 3 === 59.97  // false  ← discount never fires
```

### The Correct Fix — Integer Cents

```javascript
// Convert ONCE on input, stay in integers, convert ONLY for display
const toCents = dollars => Math.round(dollars * 100);

const total = items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + toCents(item.price), 0);
// 499 + 349 + 152 === 1000  ← always true, always exact

const display = (total / 100).toFixed(2);  // "$10.00"
```

The demo preloads Coffee + Pizza + Juice + Soda + Apple to **immediately reveal the discrepancy** between the broken and fixed totals right when the page loads!

