    bits, storing <strong>${fullFloat(4.99)}</strong> — already wrong before
    you add anything. Every arithmetic operation compounds a different rounding
    error. By the time you have a cart total, the error has accumulated across
    every multiplication and addition. <strong>=== sees the corrupted result
    exactly as-is.</strong> It is not lying to you — the number really is
